                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d825">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/15235: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Kunming</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ringwalt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kunming</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-19T10:00:00+07:00"
                            >January 19, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 19—8 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. According to informal message from special delegate, report from Milo
                    magistrate differs from that of American officers; he has been informed that two
                    competent officials, one of whom is the supervisor of district administration,
                    have been delegated to make independent investigations, and that their reports
                    will be transmitted as soon as received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ringwalt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
